                    <h2 class="null"
                      style="display: block;margin: 0;padding: 0;color: #202020;font-family: Helvetica;font-size: 22px;font-style: normal;font-weight: bold;line-height: 125%;letter-spacing: normal;text-align: left;">ASBRA Board Nominations</h2>

                    <p
                      style="margin: 10px 0;padding: 0;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #202020;font-family: Helvetica;font-size: 16px;line-height: 150%;text-align: left;">There are a number of board seats opening up on the ASBRA board and we are looking for members of the community to step up and join our team. ASBRA is an all volunteer, non-profit organization. No specific experience is required to fill a seat on the board, but a passion for bicycle racing and a willingness to give what time and talents you can is a must. The time commitment required is minimal, just a few hours per month, but the more we are able to contribute the more successful we will be in helping the bicycle racing community&nbsp;thrive.<br>
                      If you are at all interested please send an email to <a
                        href="mailto:board@asbra.org?subject=ASBRA%20Board%20Application" target="_blank"
                        style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #007C89;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">board@asbra.org</a> introducing yourself and letting us know why you think you would make a good addition to the team.
                    </p>

